Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.75,0:00:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jehovah’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.75,0:00:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we enjoy many undeserved\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.76,0:00:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and precious privileges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.76,0:00:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Among them, we bear Jehovah’s name\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.19,0:00:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and render him sacred service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.90,0:00:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As we carry out his will, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.37,0:00:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he dignifies us in a very special way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.60,0:00:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Corinthians 3:9,\Nthe apostle Paul under inspiration\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.34,0:00:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,stated that “we are God’s fellow workers.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What an honor to be a fellow worker\Nwith the Universal Sovereign,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.78,0:00:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,our loving heavenly Father! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.79,0:00:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To build appreciation for the privilege\Nof working with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.32,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to review events\Nin the life of Jonathan, a son of King Saul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:45 \Ndescribes Jonathan when it says:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.87,0:00:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For it was with God\Nthat he acted this day.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.27,0:00:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the background\Nthat led to this statement? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.01,0:01:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jonathan act, or work,\Nwith Jehovah on that day? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.05,0:01:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What lessons can we learn\Nfrom their working relationship? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.35,0:01:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And what blessings result\Nfrom being a fellow worker with God?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.56,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us begin with some background. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.53,0:01:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 12:20 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.13,0:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,records the encouraging words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.23,0:01:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,spoken by the prophet Samuel \Nto the nation of Israel: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.77,0:01:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be afraid.  . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.87,0:01:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“Only do not turn away\Nfrom following Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.24,0:01:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and serve Jehovah \Nwith all your heart.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.11,0:01:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 22 adds:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.25,0:01:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the sake of his great name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.95,0:01:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will not abandon his people.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.32,0:01:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as they remained faithful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.49,0:01:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would always be there to guide,\Nprotect, and rescue them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.70,0:01:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,These words no doubt strengthened\NJonathan to carry out Jehovah’s directive\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.73,0:01:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to subdue the enemy nations\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.90,0:02:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and take possession of the Promised Land.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.77,0:02:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At  1 Samuel chapter 13, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.38,0:02:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we read that Jonathan \Nwas assigned 1,000 men\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.98,0:02:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to attack a Philistine garrison at Geba. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.88,0:02:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Although poorly equipped,\NJonathan and his men succeeded. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.05,0:02:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This victory strengthened \NJonathan’s confidence in Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.69,0:02:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and provides a valuable lesson for us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.53,0:02:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,While we gain strength and courage\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.53,0:02:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah’s reassuring\Nwords of the Scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.57,0:02:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,our confidence in Jehovah’s support\Nbecomes even stronger\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.64,0:02:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when we successfully\Ncarry out our assignments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.67,0:02:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that may seem overwhelming.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.38,0:02:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The account then relates\Nhow the Philistines\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.71,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,were infuriated over their defeat\Nand mounted a massive counterattack. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.15,0:02:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent out raiding parties \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.15,0:02:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from their camp \Nat Michmash near Jerusalem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:02:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Many Israelite men hid out of fear, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:03:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and some even fled\Nto the other side of the Jordan River.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.50,0:03:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast,\NJonathan remained courageous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.40,0:03:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to put a stop to the raids, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.94,0:03:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he confronted the Philistine outpost\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.44,0:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at the ravine pass of Michmash. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.01,0:03:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The approach was by way of a deep gorge\Nwith nearly vertical cliffs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.48,0:03:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This would have seemed next to impossible\Nto someone unfamiliar with the area, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.42,0:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jonathan grew up in this territory\Nand apparently knew it well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His knowledge of the surroundings\Nprovides another practical lesson:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever theocratic assignment\Nwe may be given,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.60,0:03:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,putting forth time and effort \Nto get to know the terrain, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.51,0:03:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so to speak,\Nwill contribute to our effectiveness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.41,0:03:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When we show interest\Nin our assigned work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.91,0:03:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we become even more effective\Nfellow workers of Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.82,0:03:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read as Jonathan prepares\Nto take action against the Philistines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.59,0:04:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:6 states:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.23,0:04:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Jonathan said to his armor-bearer:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.93,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Come and let us cross over \Nto the outpost of these uncircumcised men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Perhaps Jehovah will act in our behalf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for nothing can hinder Jehovah\Nfrom saving by many or by few.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.54,0:04:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What contributed\Nto his confidence in Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.31,0:04:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Recall that he put faith\Nin Jehovah’s reassuring words\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.68,0:04:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,through the prophet Samuel: \N“Do not be afraid. . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of his great name,\NJehovah will not abandon his people.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.89,0:04:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He experienced Jehovah’s support \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.96,0:04:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when he struck down\Nthe Philistine garrison at Geba. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan could also\Nthink back on Israel’s history. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.37,0:04:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He could reflect\Non how Gideon and his 300 men\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.41,0:04:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,were victorious over 135,000 Midianites. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He could meditate\Non Samson killing 1,000 Philistines\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.95,0:05:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the jawbone of a donkey. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.69,0:05:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Such examples \Nwould bolster his confidence\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.69,0:05:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was working \Nwith the Almighty God, Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.26,0:05:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We too can meditate on fellow workers\Nof God recorded in the Scriptures\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as published life stories\Nof modern-day faithful servants. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Such examples\Nreinforce our faith in Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as we rely on him for success.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Another lesson comes from the response\Nof Jonathan’s armor-bearer\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.15,0:05:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Samuel 14:7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.02,0:05:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“At this his armor-bearer said to him:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.86,0:05:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do whatever your heart impels you to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.06,0:05:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Turn wherever you wish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.29,0:05:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will follow you \Nwherever your heart impels you.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is unlikely that the attendant\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would have initiated\Nthis challenging mission on his own. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.90,0:05:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan’s confident lead was a positive, \Nmotivating influence on the man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens today\Nwhen elders and overseers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.18,0:06:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,take the lead and display zeal\Nin Jehovah’s work like Jonathan? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.82,0:06:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Others in the congregation are also\Nmotivated to action by their fine example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.69,0:06:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us now read verses 8-10:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Jonathan said:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘We will cross over to those men\Nand reveal our presence to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.74,0:06:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘If they say to us,\N“Stand still until we come to you!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.11,0:06:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘we will stand where we are\Nand not go up to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.34,0:06:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘But if they say, “Come up against us!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘we will go up, because Jehovah \Nwill give them into our hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.69,0:06:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be our sign.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.52,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan once again demonstrated\Nhumble reliance on Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.29,0:06:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Later in Second Samuel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.30,0:06:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan is described\Nas “swifter than the eagles”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.50,0:06:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and “mightier than the lions.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.47,0:07:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, these qualities\Nand abilities did not cause him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.51,0:07:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to be self-reliant or overconfident. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.54,0:07:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He sought Jehovah’s direction\Nby means of a sign. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful reminder for us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of any natural abilities,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,acquired skills,\Nor experience we may have,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.69,0:07:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the key to success is seeking\NJehovah’s guidance and support. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.10,0:07:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We seek his direction\Nthrough specific prayers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.50,0:07:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible reading and meditation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and applying direction\Nfrom “the faithful and discreet slave.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.27,0:07:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We also consult \Nwith longtime faithful brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.54,0:07:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who can share their rich experience\Nas God’s fellow workers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What else can we learn\Nfrom Jonathan’s account? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.59,0:07:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Picking up at 1 Samuel 14:12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:08:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan and his armor-bearer\Nadvance toward the Philistines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.13,0:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,From their elevated location,\Nthe Philistines shout to them: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.44,0:08:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Come up to us,\Nand we will teach you a lesson!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.37,0:08:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“At once Jonathan said to his armor-bearer:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Follow me, for Jehovah will give them\Ninto the hand of Israel.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.38,0:08:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan had requested a specific sign,\Nand he got it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.62,0:08:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But it meant advancing \Nup a steep and treacherous incline \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.93,0:08:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,right into enemy hands. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.06,0:08:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone lacking complete trust \Nin Jehovah might have said,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Before proceeding,\Nperhaps we should ask for another sign,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but not Jonathan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.94,0:08:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Without hesitation,\Nhe told his attendant to follow him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.51,0:08:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah would give\Nthe enemy into their hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When we receive Jehovah’s direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.05,0:08:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we should without hesitation\Nput our hearts into the work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.85,0:08:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,confident of Jehovah’s backing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened next? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:13, 14 reports:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.43,0:09:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“And Jonathan climbed up\Non his hands and feet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.67,0:09:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“and his armor-bearer was behind him;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.60,0:09:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the Philistines began\Nto fall before Jonathan,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.04,0:09:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“and his armor-bearer was putting \Nthem to death behind him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.48,0:09:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the first attack that Jonathan\Nand his armor-bearer made,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.28,0:09:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they struck down about 20 men.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.82,0:09:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after receiving\Na clear sign from Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.82,0:09:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it took great effort. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.82,0:09:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to ‘climb up\Non their hands and feet,’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,exerting themselves\Nvigorously over rugged terrain. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.80,0:09:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The lesson? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when we receive clear direction\Nand are ready to obey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,carrying out our assignments\Nwill not always be easy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.94,0:09:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to exert ourselves vigorously, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.41,0:10:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,being willing to work hard \Nwith all of our mind, heart, and strength.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.02,0:10:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How did the Philistines react to seeing\NJehovah’s support for his people? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.92,0:10:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:15 reads:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then terror spread in the field camp \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.66,0:10:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“and among all the people of the outpost, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.23,0:10:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“and even the raiding parties were terrified. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.50,0:10:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth began quaking, \Nand a terror from God ensued.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.04,0:10:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The earthquake Jehovah caused\Nmelted the Philistines’ hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.31,0:10:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, the Israelites, even those \Nwho had previously fled in fear,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.75,0:10:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,joined the victory battle\Nover the Philistines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.02,0:10:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, when we put our hearts \Ninto theocratic assignments,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.36,0:10:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, our best Fellow Worker,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.06,0:10:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will always come through with whatever\Nwe need to accomplish his will.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.10,0:10:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is another lesson to be learned\Nfrom this exciting Bible account. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.81,0:10:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,During the height of the battle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.81,0:11:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,King Saul gave an unwise order saying:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Cursed is the man who eats\Nany food before the evening\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.72,0:11:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and until I have taken \Nvengeance on my enemies!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.22,0:11:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan, however, was not aware\Nof his father’s order\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.16,0:11:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and ate some wild honey \Nthat he had found.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.29,0:11:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Saul react when he discovered\Nthat his own son had disobeyed him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:43, 44 tells us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Saul said to Jonathan:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Tell me, what have you done?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.14,0:11:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Jonathan told him:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.68,0:11:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I merely tasted a little honey\Non the tip of the staff in my hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.99,0:11:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here I am! \NI am ready to die!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.49,0:11:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“At this Saul said:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.69,0:11:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Thus may God do and may he add to it\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.89,0:11:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do not die, Jonathan.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.96,0:11:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine, after all that Jonathan had done\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.43,0:12:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in risking his life in behalf of his people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.44,0:12:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing Jehovah grant so much success, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.64,0:12:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he is now being condemned\Nto death by his own father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.05,0:12:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How his heart must have sank in disbelief, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.72,0:12:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,disappointment, and sadness!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.45,0:12:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Would Jehovah now abandon \Nhis loyal fellow worker? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:45 reads:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.73,0:12:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the people said to Saul: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.73,0:12:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Should Jonathan die\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.93,0:12:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘—the one who brought\Nthis great victory to Israel? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.87,0:12:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘It is unthinkable! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.87,0:12:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘As surely as Jehovah is alive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.37,0:12:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘not even a single hair of his head\Nshould fall to the ground, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.61,0:12:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“for it was with God that he acted this day.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.52,0:12:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,With that the people rescued Jonathan,\Nand he did not die.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.99,0:12:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan’s success\Nprovided undeniable evidence\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.79,0:12:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was truly Jehovah’s fellow worker. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, who had been\Nat Jonathan’s side the whole time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.40,0:13:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,saw everything that had happened\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and would not allow his loyal worker\Nto die at Saul’s hands.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.57,0:13:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How comforting to know that when we\Nfaithfully carry out our assignments,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.85,0:13:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he will never forget our zealous efforts! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone as close as a father\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.05,0:13:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,fails to see and appreciate \Nthe work we do in Jehovah’s service\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.92,0:13:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or even turns against us,\NJehovah will never forget our work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He will always be there to guide, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.10,0:13:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,support, protect, and bless us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.93,0:13:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What a faith-building account \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.94,0:13:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve considered \Nin 1 Samuel chapters 13 and 14! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.41,0:13:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not take the time\Nto read these chapters for yourself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.48,0:13:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be moved to imitate\NJonathan’s excellent example of loyalty,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.62,0:13:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,courage, and obedience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.49,0:14:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to be described \Njust as Jonathan was at 1 Samuel 14:45:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.49,0:14:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For it was with God\Nthat he acted this day.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.26,0:14:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,By continuing \Nas industrious fellow workers with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.77,0:14:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we are assured\Nthat ‘through faith and patience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.87,0:14:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we will inherit the promised reward.’\N
